[div class=p 
	"This is just an attempt at setting a record for fastest TAS of a full game, and the SNES version of a certain well-known board game seemed suitable. It could be a second or two faster, but in order to have any sort of style points at all, I did some luck manipulation to make the correct solution be the one where you just keep hitting A (i.e. Col. Mustard with the Knife in the Hall).
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I used snes9x 1.43 improvement v7 with just the default recording options. No warps, passwords, glitches, or anything similar were used. This was a very easy movie to make. The worst part was just the minor tedium of finding the particular solution I wanted out of the 324 possible combinations.
	$LF
]div
